🎥 🎞️ @clickclickjim⁠⁠⁠

node.text:
@johnwardlearchitects gallery-like home is filled with impeccable crafts and art archive as an eclectic memoir of celebrated Australian architect’s adventures from childhood to now.

A film by @cocoandmaximilian. 
Music by @elliotcfmunn. 

See the full feature on yellowtrace.com.au. 

#YellowtraceArchitecture
#YellowtraceResidential
#YellowtraceInAus

node.text:
@dana.tomic.hughes had the pleasure of chatting with the mega talented @philippemalouin about his practice, the importance of design mentoring, staying true to yourself and the future of design. Philippe was recently involved with mentoring the finalists of #LexusDesignAward. Find out more at @discoverlexus, and keep an eye out for the Grand Prix winner announcement on September 1st ✌🏼
#YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #TeamYellowtrace

node.text:
Since establishing @richardsandspence in 2008, Ingrid Richards and Adrian Spence have changed the face of their home city with world-class retail, hospitality and civic architecture. Here they open up their own bangin' home in Brisbane's Bowen Hills, which flips the idea of a typical house on its head 🙌🏼 📹 by @modernister for @brickworksbp, shot by @_sirap_⁠. ⁠

#YellowtraceArchitecture #YellowtraceResidential #YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #YellowtraceXBrickworks

node.title: Take a tour through La Scala, Richards & Spence's own Brisbane home.

node.text:
✨ Michael Karakolis is the founder and director of @fibonaccistone, Australia. An extremely passionate and dedicated human being, this guy is literally obsessed, and we mean freaking OBSESSED with terrazzo. We thought it was only fitting we got to know the man behind the brand and took a deep dive inside his fascinating brain.
#YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #YellowtraceXFibonacci

node.title: In Conversation with Michael Karakolis from Fibonacci Stone.

node.text:
Conceptualized and curated by Dana Tomić Hughes of Yellowtrace, this campaign celebrates the emotive nature of Arflex's iconic and contemporary pieces and the works of some of Australia's most exiting artistic talents. “The concept was about exploring the complementary, yet opposing nature of these uniquely Australian subjects, with the boundary-pushing furniture designs that Arflex is internationally known for.” – Dana Tomić Hughes.

Find out more about this collaboration at https://www.yellowtrace.com.au/yellowtrace-x-arflex-art-design-collaboration-curated-by-dana-tomic-hughes/

node.text:
Working with noble materials and an old-world sensibility, design duo @hauvette_madani have restored this 1930s duplex to its former art deco glory. Dubbed the “Sleeping Beauty”, woodwork panels saturate the space in a honeycomb hue as eclectic furniture choices and an icy blue-grey kitchen play devil’s advocate to the dark stained envelope. Hit the 🔗 in bio for more. 🤗⁠⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷 @lucamadani⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#YellowtraceInteriors ⁠⁠⁠⁠
#YellowtraceResidential ⁠⁠⁠⁠
#YellowtraceInParis⁠⁠
⁠

node.text:
Never the ones to do things by half measures, @hermes brings another standout display during #MilanDesignWeek2021. Taking over La Pelota in Brera with a dramatic installation designed by long-term collaborator Charlotte Macaux Perelman @studiocmp, the French luxury brand unveiled their new collections for the home. For the first time ever, an audio accompaniment connects visitors to the objects. Hit the link in bio to see more 👌🏼 ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📷  @maxverret⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#YellowtraceInteriors
⁠#YellowtraceinItaly

node.text:
⁠Each room in @mccluskeystudio and @cerastribley's Bayside House has been curated to exude the qualities of a gallery. Here in the master ensuite, a decadent display of Turkish Marble can be found, lined in stone from the bathtub to the vanity bench, and to the bench in the curved marble subway tiled shower. Lush indeed. Hit the 🔗 in bio to see the rest of the house. 😍 ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Built by: @leone_constructions⁠⁠
Styled by: @marshagolemac⁠⁠
Photography: @timothykaye⁠⁠

node.text:
@astrawalkerofficial's latest and most anticipated release, Sensor Collection, employs new age technology that elevates the daily ritual of handwashing to a seamless and joyful experience. Eliminating the common frustration of finding and triggering an infrared sensor, the tap detects changing levels of capacitance to automatically activate water flow, without the need for contact. See more via the 🔗 in bio. 🙌⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Art direction & styling: @beksheppard⁠⁠
Photography: @lillie_thompson⁠⁠

With an emphasis on the unexpected, @home.studios have designed a luxe, retro-inspired boutique hotel in the historic and artistic LA neighbourhood of West Adams. Handcrafted details, custom furniture and vintage pieces mix effortlessly in this one-of-a-kind design destination. Hit the 🔗 in bio to see more.🙊⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸 @ingallsphoto⁠⁠

node.text:
Designed by @dc.ad, this sprawling bar and restaurant in Lisbon is infectiously fun. With a bright colour palette and matching neon lighting, the studio pays tribute to the Art Deco style of the 1920s with a new interpretation, balancing a contemporary ambience with a good dose of nostalgia. See more via the 🔗 in bio. 🍨⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸 @francisconogueira⁠⁠
⁠⁠

node.text:
Do you want to make a positive impact on the environment? The latest sustainable initiative by ⁠⁠@brickworksbp, Climate Active Certification, is a government-backed program that helps businesses reduce their carbon footprint and prove that they’ve achieved net-zero emissions. Hit the link in bio to learn more. 👊🏻👊🏽👊🏾⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Shown here, in the order of appearance, Australian architecture projects using Daniel Robertson certified carbon neutral bricks from Brickworks. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Project 1: @stoneyrise_wine Cellar Door⁠⁠
Architect: @cumulus_studio⁠⁠
Photography: @anjieblair⁠⁠
⁠⁠

@mccluskeystudio and @cerastribley's Bayside House presents interiors that celebrates minimalism while exuding qualities of a gallery space. With a curatorial and adventurous eye, the team introduce a glass-house extension that greatly preserves the existing house.⁠ Hit the 🔗 in bio for more. 😱⁠⁠
⁠⁠
